knowledge_graph.title: Salad dressing
knowledge_graph.description: A salad dressing is a sauce for salads. Used on virtually all leafy salads, dressings may also be used in making salads of beans, noodle or pasta salads and antipasti, and forms of potato salad.

related_questions.question: What is the healthiest salad dressing?
related_questions.snippet: Generally speaking, the healthiest salad dressing will be a vinaigrette like balsamic or oil and vinegar, while Caesar, ranch or anything with the word “creamy” will be the unhealthiest. The exception? We like products made with healthy swaps—think Greek yogurt in place of mayo or heavy cream.

related_questions.question: What are three types of salad dressings?
related_questions.snippet: Making your own dressing at home is easy and affordable, and it allows you to control the ingredients, including adding an emulsifier like egg yolk for creaminess. There are three basic salad dressings: vinaigrette, creamy, and cooked.
related_questions.title: Exploring the 3 Basic Types of Salad Dressing - The Petite Chef

related_questions.question: What is the basic formula for salad dressing?
related_questions.snippet: In general, use a ratio of three parts oil to one part vinegar, plus a small amount of an emulsifier. Add other ingredients to taste from there.
